      <div class="field field--name-field-paragraph field--type-entity-reference-revisions field--label-hidden field--count-4 field__items">
              <div class="field__item">
  <div class="contained_white_bg header-left full pad_both contained_white_full paragraph paragraph--type--row-basic paragraph--view-mode--default" id="section-8107">
            
<div class="content-wrapper">
    
            <div class="field field--name-field-column field--type-entity-reference-revisions field--label-hidden field--count-1 field__item">
  <div class="h3_header standard paragraph paragraph--type--col-text paragraph--view-mode--default" id="section-8106">
            
<div class="text-wrapper">
    
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-long-text field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field--count-1 field__item"><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 149, 76); font-family: &quot;Karbon Medium&quot;, Karbon, Arial, Helvetica, &quot;Nimbus Sans L&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 1.3rem;">The Future of Healthcare</span></p>

<p class="large color-navy">Pepper Construction’s mission is to continuously improve the quality of life through the built world. Buildings have a profound effect on how we care, connect and heal.</p>

<p class="large color-navy">The future of healthcare is a world where the built environment thrives in harmony with the natural world and one that delivers restorative health benefits to its occupants. Facilities are being designed to be more resilient and make healthcare more accessible and adaptable.</p>

<p class="large color-navy">At Pepper, we consider the long-term performance and environmental impact as we analyze project costs and plan the work. It is also critical to maintain a safe and healthy environment while we are in the process of making it better. Whether considering certificate of need requirements, applying safety precautions, sequencing a complex critical care space renovation or coordinating our work so you can respond to emergency situations, our project plans are designed to keep the patient first.</p>
</div>
      
  </div>
          </div>
</div>
      
  </div>
          </div>
</div>
